Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Wazuh services not starting

Check logs: sudo tail -f /var/ossec/logs/ossec.log
Verify configuration: sudo /var/ossec/bin/wazuh-control info
Restart services: sudo systemctl restart wazuh-manager wazuh-agent
Issue: Python scripts not detecting patterns

Verify regex patterns in content_fingerprint.py
Check file permissions: ls -la /opt/sensitive_data
Test patterns manually: grep -E '\b\d{3}-\d{2}-\d{4}\b' /opt/sensitive_data/hr/employees.txt
Issue: Alerts not appearing in Wazuh

Verify log file location in ossec.conf
Check rule syntax: sudo /var/ossec/bin/wazuh-logtest
Ensure JSON format is correct in alert logs
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated implementing Data Loss Prevention using Wazuh and content fingerprinting techniques. You learned to identify sensitive data patterns, monitor file systems for data exposure, create custom detection rules, and automate alert processing. These skills are essential for protecting sensitive information and maintaining compliance with data protection regulations like PCI-DSS and GDPR.

Key takeaways:

Content fingerprinting enables proactive sensitive data identification
Wazuh provides flexible rule-based monitoring for DLP scenarios
Automation reduces response time to potential data breaches
Pattern matching with regular expressions is fundamental to DLP systems
